Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.96,0:00:03.29,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no shape to flowing water.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.46,0:00:04.90,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no figure to flowing winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.16,0:00:06.63,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No matter what the case, the deductions are free.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.07,0:00:08.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A ghost, a pocket bell, stamps, and a music box.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.90,0:00:10.44,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All connect as one as the case is solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:12.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeing through the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:14.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The appearance of a child but the brains of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.31,0:00:16.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.73,0:01:48.17,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We took Yuuki Haruna{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s request to return a\Nmusic box to a pocket bell friend she lost contact with,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.00,0:01:52.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And we came to Ogata Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.30,0:01:55.14,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} had already passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.18,0:02:02.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That night, Ran witnessed the shadow of an old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.25,0:02:06.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s grandson, Minoru{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, was attacked by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.39,0:02:10.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And a mysterious message was sent to Haruna{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s pocket bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.32,0:02:13.26,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for you, Haruna.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.53,0:02:20.26,Title,Sign,0,0,0,,The Poignant Music Box\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.13,0:02:17.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Poignant Music Box (Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.93,0:02:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no trace of anyone sneaking in?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.50,0:02:27.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, even though the ground is soft from the rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.91,0:02:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were no footprints\Nanywhere that show signs of sneaking in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the person came in before the\Nrain, they would've left tracks when they left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.95,0:02:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there weren't any suspicious characters in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.22,0:02:44.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing that we thought was\Nodd was the back door being left open.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.72,0:02:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back door?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.72,0:02:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the lock on it is broken and it opens by itself with the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.80,0:02:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That back door is suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.10,0:02:57.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to check it out yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.71,0:03:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if someone had used the back door,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.78,0:03:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be tracks left on the soft ground, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.18,0:03:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, there aren't any...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:18.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there were footprints here, then what Ran said about\Nthe suspicious shadow wouldn't be just her imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I really saw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.10,0:03:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.63,0:03:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you move your vehicle a bit please?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.70,0:03:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.74,0:03:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's summarize the\Nevents then take another look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.41,0:03:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did the young lady see the suspicious shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.38,0:03:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.65,0:03:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A shadow of an old man with a\Ncane went by swiftly in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.69,0:03:51.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he ran into that room in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.82,0:03:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was in that room, so that can't be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.06,0:03:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I really saw the shadow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.83,0:04:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From inside this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.10,0:04:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, whose room is on this side?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.17,0:04:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that room is for my wife and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.48,0:04:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the young lady saw the\Nshadow, were you and your wife in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.85,0:04:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, my wife and I were in the kitchen with our son Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.39,0:04:24.82,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,Note: Ita has 2 meanings, 1.Ouch & 2.There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.39,0:04:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ita!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.75,0:04:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found the culprit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.36,0:04:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ouch!", not "There he is!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I stepped on a hairpin on the tatami.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.06,0:04:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hairpin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.87,0:04:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop running around!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.47,0:04:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the wounded Minoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't in the kitchen at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.45,0:04:50.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I thought Minoru was in the bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.38,0:04:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what were you three doing in the kitchen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.15,0:04:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were getting yelled at by Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:05:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying that it was rude to question\NHaruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who finally came, like an interrogation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.56,0:05:03.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like an interrogation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.50,0:05:09.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you see, I was a pocket bell buddy\Nwith Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had passed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.60,0:05:13.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they asked a lot about the details of our chats.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.11,0:05:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, along with Nii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, all three of\Nthem, again and again like an interrogation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.81,0:05:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.98,0:05:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We spoke of things like how because of\NShuugo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s influence, I began to collect stamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.82,0:05:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was able to talk about the memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.09,0:05:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I even asked if I could come again sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.49,0:05:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Minoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said something about a stamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.86,0:05:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about a hand carved stamp worth 200 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is he currently?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.50,0:05:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe those stamps have something to do with this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Minoru is in his room next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.18,0:05:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.65,0:06:01.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, even the ones in Grandpa's collection,\Nthose special hand carved stamps are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.19,0:06:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For us who believed in those stamps and\Nhad been buying them, it was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.29,0:06:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.46,0:06:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, my parents know about this as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.36,0:06:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.37,0:06:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.20,0:06:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your room next door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.10,0:06:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.74,0:06:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then... What about that room back there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.58,0:06:27.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's Grandpa and Grandma's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.78,0:06:28.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.31,0:06:29.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.18,0:06:34.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.09,0:06:36.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's the room Minoru{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was attacked by the koto in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.96,0:06:41.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That means, the way the rooms are setup is like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.43,0:06:45.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've got most of the tricks to this case now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.73,0:06:49.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The only ones left are the shadow Ran saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.33,0:06:53.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the music box Haruna{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} received\Nfrom Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} with the missing notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.91,0:06:59.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I did write out the notes based on that music box.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.38,0:07:02.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But I don't have a clue to what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.78,0:07:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't that the music for "Come, Dear Spring"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.85,0:07:07.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.89,0:07:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just my homework for music class.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.62,0:07:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, give it to me for a second, I'll draw it out for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.72,0:07:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.26,0:07:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.59,0:07:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.74,0:07:33.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.98,0:07:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.91,0:07:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.72,0:07:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, it's something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.95,0:07:44.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.79,0:07:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are these three sharps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.13,0:07:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the key signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.93,0:07:54.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Key signature!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.07,0:07:55.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If something happens, please give us a call again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.14,0:08:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.14,0:08:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we still don't know if it was a thief or a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.68,0:08:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.02,0:08:14.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:20.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, how simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.59,0:08:23.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know everything now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.73,0:08:27.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The ghost commotion that happened in this house,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.40,0:08:29.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The different pocket bell partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.63,0:08:32.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That mysterious music box's meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:39.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the location of the special collection that Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} hid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.75,0:08:44.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All that's left is to put uncle Kogorou to sleep and...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, every single time you're running around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.89,0:08:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, we're going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.16,0:08:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're leaving? But I just realized something interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.17,0:09:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at that thing over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.80,0:09:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is "that thing"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.74,0:09:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move to the right a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.71,0:09:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.29,0:09:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.45,0:09:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so it was like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.22,0:09:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, bring everyone to this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.56,0:09:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.73,0:09:35.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, before that, borrow a black\Nsheet of paper, some tape, and scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.74,0:09:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you found the thief, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.41,0:09:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thief? There wasn't anyone like that to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.98,0:09:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not going to say that it was\NFather's ghost that did it, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.15,0:09:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything that happened tonight was,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:10:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Planned by one of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.69,0:10:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.49,0:10:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it seems like the ghost thing has happened before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.63,0:10:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.97,0:10:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The music box Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} received from Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.11,0:10:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've heard about that many times from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.38,0:10:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two years ago, on Christmas, Grandpa gave it to you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.91,0:10:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I received the music box last Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.79,0:10:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Th-That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father died on December 6th last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.06,0:10:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How can that be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.69,0:10:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, Father was in the hospital\Nsince last April, and he could barely move.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey hey, what the heck is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.47,0:10:45.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:53.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone pretended to be Shuugo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and put\Nthe music box next to Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.55,0:10:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:10:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.45,0:11:03.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.06,0:11:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandpa asked me to,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.69,0:11:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying, "Even after I'm in the hospital, take care of this girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:15.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's just like my Haruna, and she is very lonely."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.97,0:11:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then does that mean ever since last spring...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I was the one talking to you in place of my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.01,0:11:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was planning to tell you everything when I met you on Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.78,0:11:35.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watching you waiting so anxiously\Nwith the red muffler as your marker,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.52,0:11:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't bring myself to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.09,0:11:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know it was me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.13,0:11:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a suspicion that you were the one\Nwho gave her the music box from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.73,0:11:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The moment I saw you at the foyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.17,0:11:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You couldn't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.30,0:11:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, you placed your hand\Non Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s shoulder and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.28,0:12:01.91,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The rumored Haruna{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} finally came.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.21,0:12:04.05,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Let's have her rest in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.58,0:12:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We hadn't introduced ourselves yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.95,0:12:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ran is roughly the same age.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.82,0:12:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even then, you were able to point out\NHaruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} without a second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.76,0:12:19.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.36,0:12:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you are the one who gave her the music box.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:29.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you, because I kept\Nquestioning her, you got mad at me and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.67,0:12:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, turn off the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.34,0:12:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.88,0:12:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.61,0:12:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Co-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.56,0:12:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Co-Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.40,0:12:55.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm over here, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:12:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd you get there so fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.10,0:12:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was here all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:05.11,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,A "Shouji" is a Japanese paper door
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be, because your shadow was just on the shouji.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.01,0:13:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the window in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.64,0:13:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hallway window?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could possibly be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.15,0:13:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a black sheet taped to the window in the shape of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.36,0:13:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle told me to put it up earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.63,0:13:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the shadow of the old man Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.66,0:13:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct, what Ran saw was just a shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.50,0:13:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tape a cutout of an old man to the hallway window.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.34,0:13:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a car comes, the light from the\Nheadlight will come through the open gate,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:46.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And portray the shadow of an old\Nman on the shouji on the opposite side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.32,0:13:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, when I saw the\Nshadow, there was a "shaa" sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably a car driving on\Nthe road that is wet from the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.63,0:14:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. If you do that, then you can still\Nshow a shadow of a person without being here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.00,0:14:03.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shirou, you could have, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.70,0:14:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I was here when you were attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.74,0:14:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can do that from this room as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.21,0:14:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using a simple setup made by some thread and a hairpin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Setup?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.18,0:14:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who set it up dropped the koto\Nfrom the ceiling in your grandfather's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.29,0:14:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It just happened to hit you on your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, Minoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was trying to\Nsecretly check the koto in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.80,0:14:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Why would I look at the koto?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably because, during dinner, you learned that the tune in the music box Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} received from your grandfather,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.54,0:14:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was what your grandmother used to love to\Nplay on the koto, "Come, Dear Spring," correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.54,0:14:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought that maybe the stamps\Nwere hidden somewhere on the koto.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.32,0:14:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if the koto fell from the\Nceiling, it isn't far to someone's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.19,0:15:01.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it wouldn't knock a person out, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.39,0:15:06.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he wanted to check the koto,\Nwouldn't he have turned the lights on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.20,0:15:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when we ran there, the room was pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't that Minoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't want to turn on the lights,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But rather, he couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.04,0:15:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the culprit's set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.68,0:15:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room was dark, and he didn't\Nknow where the string for the light was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.52,0:15:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So with no other alternative, he felt\Nhis way towards the koto on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.12,0:15:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he was planning to take it back to his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.56,0:15:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, hearing the sound of the thread\Nrubbing against the strings on the koto, he looked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.60,0:15:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the koto, unluckily, fell on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.40,0:15:44.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nii{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.10,0:15:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right, it's exactly as he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how in the world did the person drop the koto?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.91,0:15:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a simple set up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.18,0:15:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you get one long thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.18,0:16:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hang the center of that thread to the light on the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.15,0:16:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pull it through the koto under its strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.22,0:16:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then put the koto on a shelf or something temporarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.26,0:16:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, take both ends of the thread through the transom,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.26,0:16:18.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Minoru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and\NOgata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} couple's room, and finally into Ran's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.20,0:16:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then tie it in a fashion so that the two sides will not tangle,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.97,0:16:24.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And position it between the doors with a hairpin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.58,0:16:28.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, take the koto off the shelf and let\Nit hang, then the preparation is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.81,0:16:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the door to Ran's room opens even slightly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.79,0:16:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hairpin drops and the koto will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.36,0:16:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, does that mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.83,0:16:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct, the one that caused the ghost commotion\Ntonight was the one who opened the door at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.20,0:16:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it was you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.14,0:16:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.67,0:16:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.01,0:17:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably because she did not want\NHaruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to go look for those hand carved stamps.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.65,0:17:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} probably set this up during dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.85,0:17:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably when she left to prepare the futons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.82,0:17:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And upon hearing Ran's scream\Nwhen they saw the shadow of the old man,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.66,0:17:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You ran to this room, and\Ninnocently opened the door to drop the koto.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.60,0:17:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And while everyone ran to the grandfather's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.17,0:17:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took down the paper from the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.37,0:17:30.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sending that message with your\Ncell phone to Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s pocket bell,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:32.88,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for you, Haruna.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.51,0:17:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And raised the fear level.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.48,0:17:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To scare Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} enough so that\Nshe won't want to return to this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.52,0:17:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what happened to that thread used in\Nthe set up that's at least a few meters long?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.02,0:17:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom came right after we arrived at Grandpa's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.26,0:17:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She couldn't have had the time to take the paper off the window and use her cell phone as she rolled the thread back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.00,0:17:55.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a very useful item.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.90,0:17:58.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right behind Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} and the rest of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.70,0:18:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.07,0:18:08.85,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,Translator Note: Obasan means Aunt
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.07,0:18:08.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obasan probably took one side of\Nthe thread and taped it to the fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.02,0:18:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the back of this fan's blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.95,0:18:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, all she has to do is push the switch\Nand it will automatically gather the thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.59,0:18:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I can't believe you thought of such\Na complex setup when you left your seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.60,0:18:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.07,0:18:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I used their pranks when they were kids as a basis for this setup.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.58,0:18:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that shadow of the old man was also...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.78,0:18:43.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that was from me remembering\Nthat the guests that stayed here last time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mistook the shadow of the leaves\Noutside for the shadow of a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got scared of Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.96,0:18:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She even said that she's collecting stamps,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.59,0:18:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And said she would love to come back again, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:19:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the messages that were sent to\Nmy pocket bell calling me a thief was...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.87,0:19:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was me too, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.97,0:19:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's horrible, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.17,0:19:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To break Grandma's koto just because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it doesn't matter if that thing breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.98,0:19:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real koto is in storage and I switched it with a cheaper one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.85,0:19:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The new kitchen system,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.32,0:19:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your new car,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.79,0:19:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minoru's computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.79,0:19:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our finance is burnt up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we'll have to sell the music box.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.60,0:19:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I got it looked at, they said it was just an ordinary thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's weird, Grandpa said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.81,0:19:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"As a thank you to you for being me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.38,0:19:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Depending on the person who sees it, I shall\Ngive you this music box that's worth 200 million."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:19:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2-200 million?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That music box?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.49,0:19:59.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just a souvenir Dad bought\Nat the hot springs a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:02.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got played by the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.96,0:20:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That value isn't in the music box but in the missing notes it holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.40,0:20:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Japan, there is another way to\Nrepresent do-re-mi: The i-ro-ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.84,0:20:15.34,Dialogue Top,Note,0,0,0,,First line: Do re mi fa so ra ti do\NSecond Line: Ha ni ho he to i ro ha
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the missing notes are Ra, Do, and Ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you change that to Iroha representation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:28.99,Signs,Note,0,0,0,,Note: Ihai = An ash box that holds the ashes of the dead individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.58,0:20:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Ihai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.98,0:20:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That... Can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.86,0:20:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.00,0:20:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.77,0:20:42.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.23,0:20:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.07,0:20:45.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Banzai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.44,0:20:52.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:20:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we can pay off all our debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.02,0:21:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all thanks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.62,0:21:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who in the world are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Mouri Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.23,0:21:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogorou... Is that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.63,0:21:14.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.20,0:21:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was the case, then why didn't you tell us earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we knew we would have asked you\Nto help us find the stamps right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.87,0:21:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minoru wouldn't have had to get hurt too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.94,0:21:28.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This family has a lot of apologizing to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.80,0:22:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for all your troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.53,0:22:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.17,0:23:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But are you sure it's okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.94,0:23:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe those stamps were what\NShuugo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted to give you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.71,0:23:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, I've gotten something that's worth a lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.98,0:23:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandpa's pocket bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.25,0:23:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haruna{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.22,0:23:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said, "Can I still look to you for courage?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.26,0:23:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.93,0:23:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really is spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.76,0:23:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.30,0:23:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's almost summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.83,0:23:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.80,0:23:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} it's spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.51,0:23:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come, dear spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.44,0:23:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and come.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.51,0:23:43.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Heh heh, it never comes to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.36,0:23:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Difference in levels?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.63,0:24:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That little difference in levels\Nisn't something you put on your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.63,0:24:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Sonoko did tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.60,0:24:08.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He would also definitely have...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.37,0:24:15.41,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,The Invisible Weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.21,0:24:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.61,0:24:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Invisible Weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.74,0:24:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's First Case!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.25,0:24:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.82,0:24:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.82,0:24:22.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} gets sharp!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.49,0:24:23.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There's always only one truth!
